                        <div id="agenda-intro">
                          <h2>Introduction to Agenda</h2>
                          <div class="divide20"></div>
                          <h3>Agenda 1: Neocolonialism in Africa</h3>
                          <p>In the recent years, Chinese investment in Africa has increased significantly. The total trade surpassed USD 200 billion in 2013 and the Sino-African cooperation has contributed to over 20% of Africa’s economic development. As China continues to strengthen its economic influence in Africa and gain control over African resources, many nations are concerned regarding external Chinese aid and economic overdependence of African nations on China. The African Union is directly concerned with Chinese activities in the continent and must decide on its boundaries and to what extent can China intervene in Africa’s internal affairs. Delegates must consider the possibility that if the African Union does not take adequate action immediately, Africa’s domestic and foreign policy could be determined by China in the future and the continent could face the risk of Chinese exploitation.
                            </p>
                          <h3>Agenda 2: Blood Diamond Supply Chain</h3>
                          <p>African Union’s vision of the continent for the continent is hampered by high revenue sale of conflict diamonds. Diamonds in Africa are mined under rebel groups in Africa and help to fund antigovernment military action. These rebel groups are responsible for multiple human rights violations including deaths, murders and unlawful activities. Illicit diamond trade impacts all African nations and their impact is much more than just economic. African nations must find a solution to diamond trade in order progress economically, socially and politically.</p>


